Privacy Policy
Exhibit A: Phone Detective 
Developer: Vainsteel Studios · Effective date: July 16, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains what information is (and is not) processed when you play Exhibit A: Phone Detective. The Game is a fictional, offline-first detective game. All characters, phones, messages, and events depicted inside the Game are fictional game content — the Game never accesses your real messages, calls, photos, or contacts.

1. Information We Do Not Collect
Vainsteel Studios does not operate its own servers and does not collect, store, or sell any personal information. The Game requires no account, no registration, no email, and no access to your real phone data (contacts, SMS, call logs, photos, location, or microphone).
2. Data Stored on Your Device
Your game progress (solved cases, hints, settings, cosmetic choices, daily-puzzle streak) is stored locally on your device using application storage. It never leaves your device unless you use the optional cloud-save feature described below. Uninstalling the Game deletes this local data.

3. Optional Cloud Save & Achievements (Google Play Games Services)
If Google Play Games Services is available and you are signed in with your Google account, the Game can:

save your game progress to your own Google Play Games cloud storage (“Saved Games”), and
unlock achievements tied to your Play Games profile.
This data is processed by Google under the Google Privacy Policy. Vainsteel Studios cannot read, access, or share your Google account information. You can manage or delete Play Games data via your Google account settings (myaccount.google.com).

4. Advertising (Google AdMob)
The free version of the Game shows ads served by Google AdMob. AdMob may process device information (such as advertising ID, IP address, and coarse device data) to serve and measure ads, as described in the Google Ads Privacy & Terms.

Where required (e.g., EEA/UK), a consent form is shown before personalized ads are served, and you may choose non-personalized ads.
You can reset or delete your advertising ID in your device settings (Settings → Privacy → Ads).
Purchasing the “Remove Ads” or “Chief Detective Bundle” in-app product disables interstitial ads. Rewarded ads remain available only when you choose to watch them.
5. In-App Purchases (Google Play Billing)
Optional purchases are processed entirely by Google Play. Vainsteel Studios never receives your payment details (card numbers, billing address, etc.). Purchase entitlements are verified through Google Play Billing. See the Google Privacy Policy.

6. Notifications
The Game can show one optional local daily reminder (“Evidence of the Day”). This notification is scheduled entirely on your device, sends no data anywhere, and can be turned off at any time in the Game’s settings or your system notification settings.

7. Sharing Feature
The “Case Closed” share card is generated on your device. It contains only fictional game results (case title, stars, rank). It is shared only when you tap the share button and choose a destination app; the Game never posts anything on your behalf.

8. Children
The Game contains fictional crime, horror, and infidelity themes and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from anyone, including children. If you believe a child has provided personal information through a third-party service connected to the Game, please contact us and the relevant provider.

9. Security
Because the Game collects no personal data on our side, your exposure is limited to the third-party services listed above (Google AdMob, Google Play Billing, Google Play Games Services), each of which applies its own industry-standard safeguards.

10. Your Choices & Data Deletion
Local data: use the in-game “Reset” option or uninstall the Game.
Cloud saves / achievements: manage via your Google account (myaccount.google.com).
Ads personalization: device settings → Privacy → Ads, or the in-game consent form where applicable.
11. Changes to This Policy
If we change this policy, the updated version will be published at the same URL with a new effective date. Material changes will be noted in the Game’s store listing “What’s New” section.

